        <description>Query Params [Optional]
Optional params to filter data from response. Example:

fields=summary,status&amp;properties=tasks,tests&amp;expand=changelog

The fields param (which can be specified multiple times) gives a comma-separated list of fields to include in the response. This can be used to retrieve a subset of fields. A particular field can be excluded by prefixing it with a minus.

*all - include all fields
 Example: fields=*all&amp;properties=tasks,tests&amp;expand=changelog 

*navigable - include just navigable fields.
Example: fields=*navigable&amp;properties=tasks,tests&amp;expand=changelog 

summary,comment - include just the summary and comments
Example: fields=summary,comment&amp;properties=tasks,tests&amp;expand=changelog

-comment - include everything except comments (the default is *all for get-issue)
Example:  fields=*all,-comment  ( - include everything except comments)

The properties param is similar to  fields and specifies a comma-separated list of issue properties to include. Unlike  fields, properties are not included by default.
To include them all send properties=*all. You can also include only specified properties or exclude some properties with a minus (-) sign.

*all - include all properties 
Example: properties=*all

*all, -prop1 - include all properties except prop1
Example:properties=*all,-prop1

prop1, prop2 - include prop1 and code prop2 properties.
Example: properties=prop1, prop2

The expand param is used to include, hidden by default, parts of response. Example
renderedFields - field values in HTML format
names - display name of each field
schema - schema for each field which describes a type of the field
transitions - all possible transitions for the given issue
operations - all possibles operations which may be applied on issue
editmeta - information about how each field may be edited. It contains field's schema as well.
changelog - history of all changes of the given issue
versionedRepresentations - REST representations of all fields. 
 Example: expand=changelog,operations</description>
